    <div class="card">
      <h2>Aims</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Encourage community participation and creativity.</li>
        <li>Brighten public space in Bolton town centre.</li>
        <li>Give residents a visible role in shaping their local environment.</li>
        <li>Support local artists, schools and community organisations.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>Location</h2>
      <p>
        The proposed location is a suitable pavement or public square area within Bolton
        town centre, subject to council approval, safety checks and public access requirements.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>How It Would Work</h2>
      <p>
        A temporary or semi-permanent surface would be prepared for painting. Participants
        would be invited to add designs, patterns, messages or artwork within agreed guidelines.
      </p>
      <p>
        The project could take place over one day or across a weekend, with volunteers and
        organisers present to manage materials, safety and participation.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>Permissions and Safety</h2>
      <p>
        The project would require permission from the relevant local authority and any landowner.
        Materials would be chosen carefully to avoid damage, slipping hazards or obstruction.
      </p>
      <p>
        A risk assessment would be completed before the project begins.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
